Get 00UTC and 12UTC data¶

In [13]:
dfnov00 = dfnov.iloc[0::2,:]
dfnov12 = dfnov.iloc[1::2,:]
dfdec00 = dfdec.iloc[0::2,:]
dfdec12 = dfdec.iloc[1::2,:]
dfjan00 = dfjan.iloc[0::2,:]
dfjan12 = dfjan.iloc[1::2,:]
In [14]:
# interpolate the data

dfnov00 = dfnov00.interpolate(method='time', limit_area='inside')
dfnov12 = dfnov12.interpolate(method='time', limit_area='inside')
dfdec00 = dfdec00.interpolate(method='time', limit_area='inside')
dfdec12 = dfdec12.interpolate(method='time', limit_area='inside')
dfjan00 = dfjan00.interpolate(method='time', limit_area='inside')
dfjan12 = dfjan12.interpolate(method='time', limit_area='inside')

Plotting¶

In [26]:
# Plot of PBLH data for Nov, Dec and Jan for 00 UTC

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20,15))
plt.subplot(311)
plt.plot(dfnov00.index, dfnov00['mod_pbl'], label='model', color='red')
# plt.xticks(rotation= 10)
plt.plot(dfnov00.index, dfnov00['obs_pbl'], label='observed', color='blue')
#plt.xticks(rotation= 10)
plt.ylabel('PBL height (in $m$)', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('ffill', fontsize=14)
plt.legend(loc=1, prop={'size': 14})
plt.title('November 2020', fontsize=18)

plt.subplot(312)
plt.plot(dfdec00.index, dfdec00['mod_pbl'], label='model', color='red')
# plt.xticks(rotation= 10)
plt.plot(dfdec00.index, dfdec00['obs_pbl'], label='observed', color='blue')
#plt.xticks(rotation= 10)
plt.ylabel('PBL height (in $m$)', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('ffill', fontsize=14)
plt.legend(loc=1, prop={'size': 14})
plt.title('December 2020', fontsize=18)

plt.subplot(313)
plt.plot(dfjan00.index, dfjan00['mod_pbl'], label='model', color='red')
# plt.xticks(rotation= 10)
plt.plot(dfjan00.index, dfjan00['obs_pbl'], label='observed', color='blue')
#plt.xticks(rotation= 10)
plt.ylabel('PBL height (in $m$)', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('ffill', fontsize=14)
plt.legend(loc=1, prop={'size': 14})
plt.title('January 2021', fontsize=18)

fig.suptitle('PBL Height in Delhi - 00UTC', fontsize=24, y=0.99)
fig.tight_layout()
